						               													<description>A trading card game based on the &amp;quot;Berserk&amp;quot; manga series by Kentaro Miura.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal of the game is to seize control of 3 of the 5 cities in the game including the capital city or to reduce the cards in your opponent's deck to 0.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is done by playing character and effect cards at the cities' locations. All cards enter play face-down, even the cities, and you can flip only one card per turn face-up plus one card per battle. Cities are flipped face-up whenever a face-up character is at its location and flipped face-down again when the last face-up character leaves that location. Battles over cities are fought with characters with freely distributable damage in an order determined by the character's range.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Card costs are a mix of payment costs (discarding cards from your hand) and a threshold cost (the number of cities that are currently face-up).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
